29/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Justice Minister Barisa Colak has sent an official letter to his Serbian counterpart, Dusan Petrovic, demanding an urgent meeting to discuss Ilija Jurisic, a Bosnian ex-fighter who is being held in Serbia on suspicion of involvement in the 1992 Tuzla Column war crimes case.
Jurisic, arrested on May 1st, faces up to ten years in jail if found guilty.
On Wednesday Serbia's war crimes prosecutor, Vladimir Vukcevic, said the defendant would not be extradited to BiH.
(Javno.hr - 28/07/07;
Fena - 27/07/07)
